2023 was the most physically active and athletic year I had until I fractured my ankle on June 4th. I ran & hiked 5-6 miles multiple times a week, took group classes at the gym 1-2 times a day, did some boxing, & of course rollerblading. At the hospital, I was actually surprised when the Dr told me I was in great shape & healthy for my age. I know I wont be able to do those activities exactly the same without some ankle pain when I recover, but Ill continue to make my health, fitness, & happiness a priority. Ill appreciate the ability to walk & drive so much more too. Haha. This was my first 10k Spartan Trail Run in the Philippines. 🇵🇭 🦈 💪🏽

25 years as a DJ! Ill never forget being 12 years old in 7th grade practicing in the garage as my dad would be tweakin, & fixing or building some shit. Haha. Although my pops had a drug & alcohol addiction, he was truly my biggest supporter, building me custom speakers, driving me to house party gigs in middle school, & setting up & breaking down for me. Ive been DJing more than half my life. My passion for rocking crowds & entertaining people through music & a mic will never die. It’s Eternal! Especially with my crew of businessman, Im ready to hit another 25 years! Ill be the youngest spirited 62 year old youll know. www.thecrowduplifter.com #yourfavoritetattedupdj 📸 @sstudiooso
I learned real brotherhood & family values from my guys @boss_sottocapo @ej.ski. #TheRealBlackGrapes. Thankful to have quality times with quality people. Happy July 4th. 🇺🇸

Going back to 2007. I remember when @ej.ski and I were recruited into the same crew as we were both just stepping into the club scene. I was the DJ, & he was the promoter & our guy for bottle service. That was our first encounter in our early 20s. We just so happen to know of the same people in the streets. Ill never forget I needed to get something out of my car from the club. He said “Ill go with you so you wont get jumped.” That time I was funkin in the streets over some dumb ish back then, which is all good now, but at that moment I knew he was a real one Id want around me forever & Id do the same for him. We became part of BlackGrapes together & it was only right that 16 years later from 2007 to have him part of the family I created. Also a Ninong aka Godfather to my daughter, the one and only @ej.ski FKA as Pretty Boi (his rapper name.) haha. Check out his videography & photos! #TheUplifters

When the doctor says get some rest. 😂😂😂. This past month has been a challenge with a few more months counting, but my spirit, faith, & ankle has been getting strong. Cant keep an Uplifter down for too long! Haha. 📸 @sstudiooso. www.TheCrowdUplifter.com

DJing, cutting it up, making mixes, battling, doing radio, diggin for records, rocking parties every weekend, to creating my own collective has been the most positive & rewarding thing that came into my life no matter what I was going through. The friends, business, opportunities to travel, & the overall relationships Ive made with this passion has kept me young & a hustler at the same time. I can go on & on with so many stories, lessons, & experiences that this journey has took me through the last 25 years, but Ill save it for my book that Im currently working on. #thecrowduplifter #yourfavoritetattedupdj #thebiggestlittledj #theuplifters
Love and miss my baby baba so much. 2 more months. Cant wait to spoil you with hugs, kisses, & gifts.

They even placed a picture of her, which Im holding, at their celebration with all the people who couldnt be there the 2nd time around. 2nd couple Aaron & Jovy, the groom is part of a videographer/photographer company, saw me at a wedding & decided to hire me for his and I even continued to work with him after their wedding! 3rd couple Lawrence & Sunny were so cool. They planned their whole wedding by themselves & found me on IG. Haltrice & Paetrick found out about me cuz of their Officiant & church member who I went to high school with. Yo they had In n Out & Chick-fil-a for late night snacks! Clarissa & Miguel flew me out to Puerto Vallarta cuz they wanted a Bay Area DJ & I got to play a lot of Latin music as well. Kristy & Nate both from Michigan but now reside in SF, found me on IG and it was so much fun playing for a non Bay Area crowd. They loved everything. All in all, thanks to all the couples pictured here, as well as the ones from the past & future. Yall have something special I admire & I get to feel like that family friend & feel the love your guests have for yall as I uplift yall as your DJ & MC. Rob Inkies Tribute Mix! Link in bio. Happy Heavenly Bday Weekend! “In 2015, you first reached out to me through Facebook Messenger. You asked me about advertisement on the radio when I used to be on-air. You then invited me for lunch at your restaurant at the time which lead me to your tattoo shop, Inkies. Thats where my ink addiction began! As I got to know you, I admired your hustle, business ethics, & the family man you were to your wife & sons. Id stop by randomly just to chop it up with you. You always had great positive insight on life. You said once you put God first in your life, everything wasnt scattered anymore. Thanks for all the game you gave me. I miss you picking me up to go to church and having late night dinners after. Thanks for being someone I will always look up to. I even used the same font as your business with mine. Ill never forget all the encouragement you gave me. The time you told me you couldn’t wait to hold my daughter. Unfortunately she never got to meet you, but youre always her Ninong. Last months picture of what my right leg looks like. Ill be having these screws and rod in forever! The stress & depression I had to fight. It wasnt easy, but my crew The Uplifters helped me get through it all. Driving me to my gigs, driving me to get groceries, setting up our equipment, breaking it all down, & loading it back up. Had over 40 gigs I had to do & manage, but I still handled them thanks to my crew. I’ve learned so many things but the ones that stood out was 1) without health insurance, my medical bills couldve been up to $100,000. Hospitals & health care are a multimillion industry! 2) The hustle continues. The world doesnt stop for you. 3) Ive built more mental strength. You cant keep me down for too long no matter what Ive done or what people wish upon me. 4) lifes not about going hard all the time. Rest up, relax, & make time to recover. Im currently walking after 3 months since my surgery. I appreciate life even more than I once did. Thank you Lord always, my fam of friends, & followers who genuinely show love. 🥰☝🏽

Napigsa - Ilokano 🇵🇭 for strong, power & energy. Adjective. Synonyms: firm, solid, tough, loud, energetic, able, capable, stable, durable, forceful, secure 

As I travel back & forth to the Philippines often, visiting my parents provinces made me miss the Ilokano language I heard & understood as a kid. Ill always remember both my mom & dad telling me, “Napigsa datah music mo!” Translated into English for “your music is too strong/loud!” Or “Napigsa ta sao!” which is “youre talking too strong/loud!” Haha. Along with my character & energy, my music & voice will always be “Napigsa.” 💪🏽. 🪡 by @njrtattoos #YourFavoriteTattedUpDJ #TheCrowdUplifter #Pinoy #Pare #Ilokano #Ilocano

31 was definitely my heaviest. I look more than 140 lbs. I ate out everyday, worked at the radio station everyday, drank beers & liquor and ate good at my gigs every weekend, sometimes weekday gigs too. My point is even after 4 months on a fractured ankle, with no ability to walk, drive, workout, etc, I came back in about 2 months and lost 21 lbs, weighing less when I got injured. Even with some difficulty walking sometimes. Dr said I can go back to activities I did, so I went after it, with caution. 🙏🏽. Im not the type to make up excuses. Now that Im older, I became even healthier, smarter, & wiser. Like my forehead tat reads. #Napigsa 🇵🇭🫡 (Ilocano for strong, solid, firm)
